model_explanation: the prosodic focus on “TOM” in S1 means Sam did not give apples to anyone else but Tom. However, S2 says Sam gave Tom another kind of fruit (grapes), which does not contradict the focus of S1. But since “only” in S1 restricts the recipient, if the statement shifts to giving grapes as well, it does not explicitly affect the entailment about the specific recipient for apples. The contradiction arises in the sense that S1 suggests exclusivity that’s now challenged by another gift, creating indirect contradiction about exclusivity.
the focus on “TOM” in S1 means that Sam gave oranges to Tom and no one else. Therefore, it entails that Sam did not give oranges to Bill or anyone else, making S2 an entailment.
the focus on “MARY” in S1 indicates that Sam gave bananas only to Mary and no one else. This naturally entails that Bill did not receive bananas.

the focus on “MARY” in S1 means Sam gave apples only to Mary and no one else. However, S2 says Sam gave Mary another type of fruit (bananas), which contradicts the exclusivity implied by S1 (that Mary only received apples and nothing else).
the focus on “SUE” in S1 means that Sam gave apples to Sue and no one else. This entails that Rob didn’t get apples, which aligns with S2.

the focus on “BILL” in S1 means that Sam only gave bananas to Bill, and no one else got bananas. However, S2 says Sam also gave Bill grapes, which contradicts the exclusivity that Bill only received bananas.
the focus on “ROB” in S1 means Sam gave grapes only to Rob. This entails that Rob did not receive any other fruit, including apples, making S2 consistent with S1.
the focus on “SUE” in S1 means that Sam gave grapes only to Sue and no one else. If Sam also gave grapes to Tom, that contradicts the exclusivity implied by S1.
the focus on “ELLEN” in S1 means that Sam gave grapes only to Ellen and no one else. Therefore, the statement that Rob didn’t get grapes is consistent with the entailment from S1.
the focus on “MARY” in S1 means that Sam gave grapes only to Mary and no one else. If S2 states that Mary also got bananas, this contradicts the exclusivity of what Mary was given in S1.
